parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Throttle Body Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body sensor can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine RPMs suddenly increase to high levels
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the throttle pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle takes off rapidly
and the brakes may not be effective in slowing down the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly while cruise control is engaged
the throttle pedal sticks to the floor
and the brakes may not be effective in slowing down the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle air control valve can cause the engine to idle excessively, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine RPMs suddenly increase to high levels
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
and the throttle pedal sticks to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not latch or stay locked
the buckle mechanism collapses
the buckle does not stay in the locked position
the buckle unlatches on its own
the seat belt does not retract back to its original position
the seat belt sticks and does not retract unless played with.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence or malfunction of rear seat belts can increase the risk of injury or fatality to rear seat passengers in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear seat does not have seat belts
the rear lap belts stick and do not retract unless played with.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling while turning can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially when entering intersections.
symptoms: Engine shuts down when turning left or right

especially when releasing the foot brake and applying gas; stalling may occur when the steering wheel is slightly turned; engine may catch again if the driver quickly applies more gas and turns the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty wiring harnesses can cause electrical fires, engine stalling, and other safety issues.
symptoms: Wiring harnesses with crimp connectors covered in duct tape
which can dry rot and provide no protection; wires grounding out
causing small fires; smoke coming from the interior of the vehicle; burned wires in the handbrake area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and other safety issues.
symptoms: Electrical system failure; instrument cluster module failure; vehicle shutting down; wires melting; smoke coming from under the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition system failures can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and other safety issues.
symptoms: Engine stalling; ignition switch failure; starter relay switch failure; alternator failure; cruise control failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaking fuel injectors can cause fuel to spray onto the hot exhaust system, leading to a high risk of engine fires, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Strong fuel smell
throttle sticking
engine surging
fuel leaking into the engine compartment
rough engine operation
stalling
and in extreme cases
engine fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the fuel injection system can lead to fuel leaks, which can cause engine fires, and the faulty fuel filter can compromise engine performance and safety.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
fuel smell
rough engine operation
and engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel indicator can lead to drivers running out of fuel, causing inconvenience, and potentially leading to safety risks, especially on highways.
symptoms: Fuel indicator shows incorrect fuel levels
leading to unexpected fuel depletion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates suddenly to high RPMs
especially in heavy traffic or crawl speed conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improperly crimped wiring at the fuel pump end can cause overheating, leading to electrical fires and potential engine damage.
symptoms: Burning smell
overheating
and electrical fires.
